                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.Consultation(2)/414: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the American Delegate</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hull</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-24T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 24, 1940—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>25. For White from the Secretary of the Treasury. Reference your 9, July 23, 6
                    p.m. I am willing to go along provided the Government and Central Bank of each
                    particular country would guarantee individually and collectively the gold loan.
                    [Morgenthau.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
